data.title: Fern Emmett
data.meta_description: Fern Emmett. Actress: Ten Nights in a Bar-Room. Fern Emmett was born on 22 March 1896 in Oakland, California, USA. She was an actress, known for Ten Nights in a Bar-Room (1931), Cinderella Swings It (1943) and Scattergood Baines (1941). She was married to Henry Roquemore. She died on 3 September 1946 in Hollywood, Los Angeles, California, USA.
